Grenadaâ€™s airport re-opened on 1 July to charter flights only and on 15 July to regional commercial flights, and is scheduled to re-open to commercial flights from UK, Europe and Canada from 1 August. British Airways and Virgin Atlantic are yet to resume their schedules to and from Grenada. Passengers should keep in touch with airlines to see when flights are returning.
BA resumed a limited schedule to Bridgetown from 18 July. Caribbean Airlines started a regional service from Grenada and Saint Vincent to Barbados from 22 July which provides an option to connect to these BA flights. Other regional airlines are expected to start flights from Grenada to Bridgetown soon. These include One Caribbean and Inter Caribbean
There are private charter companies including Executive Air who operate between Grenada and Barbados. It is also possible to book a private charter with Airawak from Grenada to Martinique from where connections to the UK with Air France via Paris, are available.
If you are considering travelling by these routes you are responsible for ensuring that you meet all requirements for entry and onward travel of all countries and territories. Please review the relevant country pages on FCDO Travel Advice before travel and check carefully any requirements for COVID testing before departure, to ensure that your test certificate will be accepted in your arrival country.
Future options
This travel advice will be updated when further departure options become available.
You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. If departure options are available but you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information, you should contact Corporate Travel Management (CTM). CTM are a commercial partner of the FCDO and are authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCDO.
Returning to the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK. From 10 July those entering the UK from Grenada will not have to self- isolate on arrival.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British High Commission in Bridgetown, Barbados, on Facebook and Twitter.
